cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper describes the development of a deep convolutional neural network for predicting cognitive decline in Alzheimer's disease patients using PET imaging. This work involves computer vision (analysis of PET images), machine learning (development of a deep neural network), and artificial intelligence (use of deep learning for prediction). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence for prediction, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of computational neuroscience, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of PET imaging for cognitive assessment, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction, so cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible sub-category.
